meanings.definition: To overpower or defeat someone in physical strength or ability.
meanings.sent1: The wrestler was outmuscling his opponent in the ring.
meanings.sent2: She was outmuscling her competitors in the weightlifting competition.
meanings.sent3: The tiny kitten was outmuscling the big dog in a playful wrestling match.
meanings.sent4: The waves crashed against the shore, outmuscling the rocks in their relentless power.
meanings.sent5: The superhero outmuscling the villain made for an exciting showdown.

meanings.definition: To surpass or outperform someone in terms of physical strength or ability.
meanings.sent1: The new athlete was outmuscling the experienced players on the team.
meanings.sent2: He was outmuscling his personal best in the gym.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel was outmuscling the birds in reaching the bird feeder first.
meanings.sent4: Her determination was outmuscling any obstacles in her path to success.
meanings.sent5: The engine roared to life, outmuscling any doubts about its power.
